          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are TailSpark supplements suitable for all dogs?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. All formulas are vet-formulated for dogs of all breeds and ages. If your dog has a medical condition, is pregnant, or is currently on medication, consult your veterinarian before starting any new supplement.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q_1_2": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What form do the supplements come in?",
            "content": "<p>All TailSpark supplements are soft chews - a convenient, tasty format that's easy to give daily. No mixing into food, no capsules, no measuring. Most dogs take them happily right from your hand.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q_1_3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are the chews grain-free?",
            "content": "<p>Our chews are free of corn and wheat. Some formulas contain oat flour or rye flour. The full ingredient list for each product is available on its product page.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q_1_4": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are there any artificial flavors or colors?",
            "content": "<p>No. All TailSpark supplements are free of artificial flavors and colors. Some formulas use natural duck flavor to make them more appealing to dogs.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q_1_5": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I give my dog multiple TailSpark supplements at the same time?",
            "content": "<p>Yes - TailSpark supplements are designed to work well together. Many customers combine Hip &amp; Joint with Skin &amp; Coat, or Probiotic with Multivitamin. All formulas are carefully developed to complement each other.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q_1_6": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are these supplements suitable for puppies and senior dogs?",
            "content": "<p>Yes, all formulas are designed for dogs of all ages. Dosing is based on weight, so follow the directions on the product page for the appropriate serving size.</p>"
          }
        },
