        "q_3_3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is a cGMP, FDA-Registered Food Facility?",
            "content": "<p>cGMP stands for Current Good Manufacturing Practices - a standard set by the FDA that ensures products are consistently produced under strict quality controls. An FDA-Registered Food Facility means the manufacturing site is registered with and subject to inspection by the FDA. Together, these standards mean every batch of TailSpark supplements is produced in a controlled, documented, and quality-verified environment.</p>"
